## Prerequisites
* A Google Account (for Gmail and Google Sheets).
* A free [Gemini API Key from Google AI Studio](https://aistudio.google.com/app/apikey).

## Setup Instructions

### 1. Create the Google Sheet
1. Create a new Google Sheet.
2. Name it something like "Daily Research Tracker".
3. *(Optional)* Add headers to the first row: `Date | Category | Title & Source | Summary | Relevance/Angle | Link`.

### 2. Add the Code
1. In your Google Sheet, click on **Extensions > Apps Script**.
2. Delete any code in the editor and paste the contents of `Code.gs` (provided below).
3. Replace the placeholder `'PASTE_YOUR_API_KEY_HERE'` with your actual Gemini API Key. *(Do not share this key publicly!)*
4. Click the **Save** icon (floppy disk).

### 3. Set Up Automation (Triggers)
To make this run automatically every day:
1. In the Apps Script editor, click the **Clock icon** (Triggers) on the left sidebar.
2. Click **+ Add Trigger** in the bottom right.
3. Choose which function to run: `runDailySSRNTracker`
4. Select event source: `Time-driven`
5. Select type of time based trigger: `Day timer`
6. Select time of day: e.g., `6am to 7am` (so your briefing is ready when you wake up).
7. Click **Save** and grant the necessary Google permissions when prompted.

